outputs.description: Children and adolescents have access to comprehensive protection services, with improved coordination and functioning inprioritized areas, thereby reducing their vulnerability and contributing to the fulfilment of their rights, particularly to theright to development.
PRIOR-YEAR COMMITMENTS

In two years, children, women and their families in the most vulnerable communities in at least 50% of the municipalities in thecommonwealth of municipalities in the Chaco region (5) and North Potosí (7) have improved their resilience in emergencies byimplementing a training and practice plan with municipal technical teams. Chaco: Machareti, Huacaya, Huacareta, Muyupampa yMonteagudo. Norte Potosí: Caripuyo, Sacaca, Chayanta, Pocoata, San Pedro de Buena Vista y Torotoro

IR 2.2: Safe hygiene habits are practiced by the communities and schools in which UNICEF works.

Pregnant women and newborns in urban and rural areas have Access to HIV prevention, diagnostics and treatment services.
Children and mothers in 6 intervention Departments have access to quality, friendly health services that have gender andintercultural approaches that humanize care, including community strategies.
Families in 52 intervention municipalities adopt healthy practices to achieve adequate nutrition in early childhood, includingpregnant women.
Pregnant women, children and adolescents in at-risk populations have access to health and nutrition services.

Children and adolescents have access to a national child protection system during emergency situations that reduce the risks ofviolence, abuse, exploitation, discrimination and vulnerabilities of being separated from their parents.
Children and adolescents have access to child protection and promotion services, as well as institutional and legal frameworks thatprotect them.
